        "created_at": "2024-09-05T16:00:57.519Z",
        "cooked": "<p>If I open a chat to write a new message, I see the following bar with the text input:</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/b/c/bc5b79b12562844a846f2156b891b14baaaae9a9.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/bc5b79b12562844a846f2156b891b14baaaae9a9\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/b/c/bc5b79b12562844a846f2156b891b14baaaae9a9_2_690x253.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"qShKt4jxmrPxIJri9KyZgGjtlQR\" width=\"690\" height=\"253\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/b/c/bc5b79b12562844a846f2156b891b14baaaae9a9_2_690x253.jpeg, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/b/c/bc5b79b12562844a846f2156b891b14baaaae9a9.jpeg 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/b/c/bc5b79b12562844a846f2156b891b14baaaae9a9.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"101010\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">959×352 18 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>Besides the text input, I can see four symbols: a +, a square that looks like a paper, a camera and a microphone.</p>\n<p>While many people might be very happy with this design, I‘m not. Because I have to see them everytime I open a chat - but I use none of them.</p>\n<p>Let‘s start with the camera.<br>\nSignal does not have access to my camera. I make photos with another app, and while I use audio calls, I never made a video call.<br>\nWould it be an idea, that Signal checks, if the camera permission is enabled, and otherwise the camera symbol is not being shown?</p>\n<p>The microphone…<br>\nThis only makes sense, if you actively send voice messages.<br>\nI do not do that. Never.<br>\nIt would really be nice to have an option to hide this symbol.</p>\n<p>Stickers…<br>\nI don’t use stickers, I have no stickers installed. An option ”use stickers“ would be nice, so if you don’t use it, you don’t have to see this.</p>\n<p>The plus…<br>\nI don’t really mind that symbol so much, but I don’t use it.<br>\nWhen I send photos, I either use the old fashioned iOS way to go to the photos app, select the photos I want to send, and then share them with Signal. Sometimes I just copy and paste photos to Signal.<br>\nSame with files. I select them in a files app, and share them with Signal.</p>\n<p>Four symbols, none for me. This means, the UX for me is not that great.</p>",
