        "created_at": "2025-04-27T08:34:32.965Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I wonder, would it be possible to hide the camera and microphone icons when the respective device access is disabled.<br>\nOne possible downside would be users who accidentally deny access and are then unable to find the icon again until they find out where to allow access again. But I don’t know if this is really a problem.</p>\n<p>Also, there could simply be options in the chat menu to hide the sticker, voice message and camera buttons, but I’m afraid that would clash with one of Signals design philosophies.</p>",
