        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/cuehd/{size}/42510_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-04-27T11:00:28.479Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Wopfi\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"62773\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/wopfi/48/1243_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Wopfi:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>would it be possible to hide the camera and microphone icons when the respective device access is disabled.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I doubt that an app could distinguish between “allow never” versus “allow this time” permissions choices. If users prefer choosing “allow this time”, the app might not be able to present the icon to permit the choice.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Wopfi\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"62773\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/wopfi/48/1243_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Wopfi:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>there could simply be options in the chat menu to hide the sticker, voice message and camera buttons</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I’m all for this.</p>",
